During his speech, Tonoyan stated that regional conflicts do not have military solution, and neither military rhetoric nor attempts to involve new states in these conflicts. He also called the developing military-political events in the region a conflict of geopolitical interests. 

Furthermore, he noted that the presence of Russia in the region and the deepening of military and political cooperation between Armenia and Russia are the most important deterrents that contribute to the maintenance of regional peace and stability. 

Earlier, Tonoyan confirmed that he is ready to meet Azerbaijani Defense Minister Zakir Hasanov during the joint meeting in Moscow, noting though that he “doubts that he [Zakir Hasanov] will show such willingness”.

source: Press Secretary Shushan Stepanyan

